endpointAlgorithms.name: Primary: Overall Survival (OS)
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: Date of Death - Date of Randomization
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Statistically significant increase in OS compared to control
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: Overall Survival (OS) is defined as the time from randomization to death due to any cause.

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Progression-Free Survival (PFS)
inputs: Date of first documented disease progression
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: min(Date of Progression, Date of Death) - Date of Randomization
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Statistically significant increase in PFS compared to control
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: Progression-Free Survival (PFS) is defined as the time from randomization to the first documented disease progression per RECIST 1.1 or death due to any cause, whichever occurs first.

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Objective Response Rate (ORR)
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: (Total number of subjects with CR + Total number of subjects with PR) / Total subjects
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Proportion of subjects achieving CR or PR per RECIST 1.1
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: Objective Response Rate (ORR) is defined as the proportion of subjects in the analysis population who have a complete response (CR) or partial response (PR).

derivedVariables.name: Percent Change in Body Surface Area
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: Body surface area measured at baseline prior to first dose

derivedVariables.name: Recalculated Paclitaxel Dose
derivedVariables.derivationRule: If Percent Change in BSA from baseline or last recalculation is >= 10%, dose must be recalculated as (80-100 mg/m2 * Current BSA). If < 10%, recalculation is optional.

derivedVariables.name: Recalculated Docetaxel Dose
derivedVariables.derivationRule: If Percent Change in BSA from baseline or last recalculation is >= 10%, dose must be recalculated as (75 mg/m2 * Current BSA). If < 10%, recalculation is optional.

derivedVariables.name: Recalculated Irinotecan Dose
derivedVariables.derivationRule: If Percent Change in BSA from baseline or last recalculation is >= 10%, dose must be recalculated as (180 mg/m2 * Current BSA). If < 10%, recalculation is optional.
